title: The best reactions and moments of the Democratic debate | www.ajc.com
text:
Here's the best analysis, commentary and reactions from the first Democratic presidential primary debate .
Let's start out with the fancy charts and statistics.
Good night, folks! Here's a wrap-up of the #DemDebate : http://t.co/aqlXesUNNv pic.twitter.com/GhLZc39VCm
— FiveThirtyEight (@FiveThirtyEight) October 14, 2015 How much time each candidate spoke for during the #DemDebate http://t.co/FLxjxpOj6O pic.twitter.com/fikjvwQSWX
— The New York Times (@nytimes) October 14, 2015 Did you feel the Bern during last night’s #DemDebate ? Twitter users certainly did: http://t.co/h3Gf4MlvPW pic.twitter.com/3ae50om0Td
— Forbes (@Forbes) October 14, 2015 Here's a sampling of commentary.
Hillary seems to be winning the most important debate tonight: The one in the Biden household.
— Jon Ralston (@RalstonReports) October 14, 2015 In a sense, both main candidates succeeded with their base. For Clinton, it was the media. For Sanders, it was Democratic primary voters.
— Patrick Ruffini (@PatrickRuffini) October 14, 2015 I hope they’ve got a stoned journalist to ask the post questions like they had the black guy ask race question & the hispanic on immigration
— Philip Gourevitch (@PGourevitch) October 14, 2015 Oh, the irony: every question in the spin room is about Bernie's call to stop talking about Hillary's emails.
— Molly Ball (@mollyesque) October 14, 2015 When was the last time the post-event consensus was so uniformly positive for Hillary?
— Gabriel Debenedetti (@gdebenedetti) October 14, 2015 Casinos have cleaner books than O'Malley's crime numbers. You and I both know it.
— Esquire Magazine (@esquire) October 14, 2015 Donald Trump live-Tweeted the debate. Of course we can't help ourselves so here's a sampling of what he posted.
Sorry, there is no STAR on the stage tonight!
— Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) October 14, 2015 Notice that illegal immigrants will be given ObamaCare and free college tuition but nothing has been mentioned about our VETERANS #DemDebate
— Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) October 14, 2015 Wow, I am giving a speech on OAN. Much more exciting than debate!
— Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) October 14, 2015 Let's wrap it up with a few jokes.
Jim Webb really let himself go pic.twitter.com/8gaihy1pCt
— Matthew Zeitlin (@MattZeitlin) October 14, 2015 Clinton: ".. the NRA, Iran, the entire Republican Party--" Cooper: "Thank you. Senator--" Clinton: "I'M NOT DONE LISTING MY ENEMIES."
— Jonathan Chait (@jonathanchait) October 14, 2015 Back at home, a smiling Lincoln Chaffee exhales and leans over to spend another long night tending to his butterfly collection
— Joshua Green (@JoshuaGreen) October 14, 2015
